### 1. Create author
POST http://localhost:8081/api/v1/authors
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "Ivan Franko",
  "email": "ivan@example.com"
}

### 2. Create category
POST http://localhost:8081/api/v1/categories
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Technology"
}

### 3. Create content
POST http://localhost:8081/api/v1/contents
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Microservices in Media Platform",
  "body": "This content was created in content-service.",
  "authorId": 1,
  "categoryId": 1
}

### 4. Add comment through interaction-service
POST http://localhost:8082/api/v1/comments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "contentId": 1,
  "authorId": 2,
  "text": "Interesting article"
}

### 5. Add rating through interaction-service
POST http://localhost:8082/api/v1/contents/1/ratings
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "authorId": 2,
  "score": 5
}

### 6. Check content after rating sync
GET http://localhost:8081/api/v1/contents/1

### 7. Moderate through moderation-service
POST http://localhost:8083/api/v1/contents/1/moderations
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "resolution": "APPROVED",
  "reason": "Content meets moderation rules"
}

### 8. Check content after moderation sync
GET http://localhost:8081/api/v1/contents/1

### 9. Failure scenario
### Stop content-service, then run:
POST http://localhost:8082/api/v1/comments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "contentId": 1,
  "authorId": 3,
  "text": "This request should fail when content-service is down"
}
